曇りの日、ツツジが咲いていた。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Gardens" /><category term="Flowers" /><category term="Shrines" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Azaleas in bloom on a cloudy day. 曇りの日、ツツジが咲いていた。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_IMG_3670.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_IMG_3670.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Alley・路地</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260420/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Alley・路地" /><published>2026-04-20T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-04-20T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/alleyway</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260420/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
A wet alleyway at dusk.
</p>
<p class="jp">
夕暮れの濡れた路地。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Architecture" /><category term="Dusk" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A wet alleyway at dusk. 夕暮れの濡れた路地。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R01253.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R01253.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Tamanoyu・玉の湯</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260419/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Tamanoyu・玉の湯" /><published>2026-04-19T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-04-19T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/tamanoyu</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260419/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Entrance to the <a href="https://kyoto-tamanoyu.com/" target="_blank">Tamanoyu sento</a> (public bath) in central Kyoto, opened in 1894. Their mostly older customers' bicycles are parked symmetrically alongside the entrance.
</p>
<p class="jp">
明治27年にオープンした京都中京区にある銭湯「<a href="https://kyoto-tamanoyu.com/" target="_blank">玉の湯</a>」の入り口。主に年配のお客さんの自転車が入口に左右対称に停まっている。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Architecture" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Entrance to the Tamanoyu sento (public bath) in central Kyoto, opened in 1894. Their mostly older customers' bicycles are parked symmetrically alongside the entrance. 明治27年にオープンした京都中京区にある銭湯「玉の湯」の入り口。主に年配のお客さんの自転車が入口に左右対称に停まっている。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_IMG_3621.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_IMG_3621.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Komainu・狛犬</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260418/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Komainu・狛犬" /><published>2026-04-18T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-04-18T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kamainu</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260418/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
A <em>komainu</em> (lion dog) sculpture at Gyogan-ji temple, with a red and gold brocade bib (<em>yodarekake</em>).
</p>
<p class="jp">
行願寺にある狛犬の像。赤と金の錦の涎掛けをつけている。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Temples" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A komainu (lion dog) sculpture at Gyogan-ji temple, with a red and gold brocade bib (yodarekake). 行願寺にある狛犬の像。赤と金の錦の涎掛けをつけている。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R01243.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R01243.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Soft Pink・ソフトピンク</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260412/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Soft Pink・ソフトピンク" /><published>2026-04-12T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-04-12T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/last-sakura</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260412/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
One last post of cherry blossoms for the season, taken on Arashiyama's Nakanoshima Island in soft, buttery sunlight. Shot with Fujichrome Velvia 100 film.
</p>
<p class="jp">
嵐山の中之島で柔らかく降り注ぐ日差しの中で撮影した。フジクローム・ベルビア100フィルムで撮影した。

</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Sakura" /><category term="Film" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[One last post of cherry blossoms for the season, taken on Arashiyama's Nakanoshima Island in soft, buttery sunlight. Shot with Fujichrome Velvia 100 film. 嵐山の中之島で柔らかく降り注ぐ日差しの中で撮影した。フジクローム・ベルビア100フィルムで撮影した。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_DSC_2644_edit_edit-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_DSC_2644_edit_edit-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Yaezakura・八重桜</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260411/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Yaezakura・八重桜" /><published>2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/yaezakura</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260411/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
The last of the cherry blossoms, the lush, "multi-layered cherry blossoms" <em> (yaezakura) </em>  in bloom at Ryoanji temple.
</p>
<p class="jp">

最後の桜、龍安寺に咲いた分厚い八重桜。

</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Sakura" /><category term="Temples" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The last of the cherry blossoms, the lush, "multi-layered cherry blossoms" (yaezakura) in bloom at Ryoanji temple.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R01137_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R01137_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Amanohashidate・天橋立</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260410/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Amanohashidate・天橋立" /><published>2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/amanohashidate</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260410/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Looking down at the Amanohashidate sandbar and the Asokai Sea, one of Japan's three scenic views. Taken next to a cherry tree at Kasamatsu Park.
</p>
<p class="jp">

日本三景のひとつ、天橋立砂州と阿蘇海を見下ろす。傘松公園の桜の木の横で撮影。

</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Water" /><category term="Views" /><category term="Aerial" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Looking down at the Amanohashidate sandbar and the Asokai Sea, one of Japan's three scenic views. Taken next to a cherry tree at Kasamatsu Park.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R01086_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R01086_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Ine Bay・伊根湾</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260409/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Ine Bay・伊根湾" /><published>2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/ine</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260409/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
A tour boat crosses the natural harbor of Ine Bay, a fishing village on the Tango Peninsula.
</p>
<p class="jp">

丹後半島の漁師町、伊根湾の天然の港を遊覧船が進む。

</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Water" /><category term="Views" /><category term="Boats" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A tour boat crosses the natural harbor of Ine Bay, a fishing village on the Tango Peninsula.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R01055.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R01055.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Kotohikihama Sunset・琴引浜の夕日</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260408/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Kotohikihama Sunset・琴引浜の夕日" /><published>2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kotohikihama</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260408/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
A cloudy sunset into the Sea of Japan, in the Kyotango area at the north end of Kyoto Prefecture.
</p>
<p class="jp">

京都府の北端、京丹後地方の日本海に沈む曇天の夕日。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Sunset" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A cloudy sunset into the Sea of Japan, in the Kyotango area at the north end of Kyoto Prefecture.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R00971.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R00971.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Yura River・由良川</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260407/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Yura River・由良川" /><published>2026-04-07T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-04-07T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/tango</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260407/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
A Tantetsu Miyama Line train passes over the Yura River in Miyazu, Kyoto Prefecture.
</p>
<p class="jp">

京都府宮津市の由良川を、丹鉄美山線の列車が渡っている。

</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Trains" /><category term="Rivers" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A Tantetsu Miyama Line train passes over the Yura River in Miyazu, Kyoto Prefecture.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R00842.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2604_A7R00842.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry></feed>